Literature Survey (01/09/2025 to 13/09/2025)

Background:
Voice-based AI systems are widely used in the form of Google Assistant, Siri, and Alexa. They improve user experience and accessibility. Our project aims to create a lightweight, system-specific speech control model.

Existing Systems:

Siri – Apple’s voice assistant for iOS/macOS.

Google Assistant – Cross-platform voice AI by Google.

Amazon Alexa – Smart home voice interface.

Microsoft Cortana – System-level speech control assistant.

Dragon NaturallySpeaking – Speech-to-text software.

Limitations of Existing Systems:

Require high internet connectivity.

Limited system-level control.

High cost for commercial solutions.

Dependency on specific ecosystems.
